{
  "texts": [
    "Precessing neurons have score greater than 0.3 and negative slope steeper than -72 °/field.",
    "W-maze data.",
    "Single neurons in Fig. 7A -H are preprocessed from the CRCNS hc-6 dataset as described in Supplementary Information 25.",
    "For each neuron, we bin spikes into 2 turn directions and phase bins of width 45 ∘.",
    "Since our prediction compares sparse and dense information conveyed by the same neurons, we require at least 5 spikes within each phase value to allow for accurate estimation of position information across all theta phases."
  ]
}